SUMMARY:Day 1: Seattle → Victoria\, BC
LOCATION:Oak Bay anchorage or Victoria Harbour
DESCRIPTION:70.4 NM · ~3.5 hrs\nOvernight: Oak Bay anchorage or Victoria Harbour\n\nNote: Depart early — US/Canada customs by water can involve a wait. Passports for everyone aboard.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=1
UID:day-1-20260706@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260707
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260708
SUMMARY:Day 2: Victoria → Salt Spring Island → Vancouver
LOCATION:False Creek Fisherman's Wharf or Granville Island Marina
DESCRIPTION:67.7 NM · ~4.5 hrs\nOvernight: False Creek Fisherman's Wharf or Granville Island Marina\n\nNote: Depart Salt Spring by 1:30–2pm to arrive Vancouver before evening. If you time it for a Saturday\, the Ganges market is not to be missed.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=2
UID:day-2-20260707@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260708
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260709
SUMMARY:Day 3: Vancouver — Layover
LOCATION:False Creek (same marina)
DESCRIPTION:Overnight: False Creek (same marina)\n\nNote: Use today to nail down Malibu Rapids timing. Plan your Day 4 departure from Vancouver to arrive exactly at the slack window — not the other way around.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=3
UID:day-3-20260708@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260709
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260710
SUMMARY:Day 4: Vancouver → Princess Louisa Inlet
LOCATION:Princess Louisa Marine Provincial Park (anchor / stern-tie)
DESCRIPTION:87.3 NM · ~5.1 hrs\nOvernight: Princess Louisa Marine Provincial Park (anchor / stern-tie)\n\nNote: Malibu Rapids is the most critical passage of the trip. No safe transit exists except within ±30 min of slack. Build the entire day around this window.\n\nTODO: Figure out if I’m okay for stern-tying\nTODO: Is the dock there still under construction?
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=4
UID:day-4-20260709@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260709T070000
DTEND:20260709T120800
SUMMARY:🚢 Vancouver BC → Princess Louisa Inlet
DESCRIPTION:87.3 NM · ~5h 8m\nVancouver BC → Princess Louisa Inlet
UID:route-dbd45f11-9989-4b6f-ac88-9c92eae8af59@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260710
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:Day 5: Princess Louisa Inlet — Layover
LOCATION:Princess Louisa Marine Provincial Park
DESCRIPTION:Overnight: Princess Louisa Marine Provincial Park\n\nNote: One of the most spectacular anchorages in the world. Fully protected from swell. Don't rush it.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=5
UID:day-5-20260710@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260711
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260712
SUMMARY:Day 6: Princess Louisa → Prideaux Haven (Desolation Sound)
LOCATION:Prideaux Haven\, Desolation Sound Marine Park
DESCRIPTION:81.4 NM · ~8.1 hrs\nOvernight: Prideaux Haven\, Desolation Sound Marine Park\n\nNote: Prideaux fills fast in July — arrive by early afternoon. Tenedos Bay (adjacent) is an excellent overflow anchorage.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=6
UID:day-6-20260711@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260711T090000
DTEND:20260711T170800
SUMMARY:🚢 Princess Louisa Inlet → Prideaux Haven
DESCRIPTION:81.4 NM · ~8h 8m\nPrincess Louisa Inlet → Prideaux Haven
UID:route-2aa02d77-5b47-45f1-ab61-189a591cd862@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Day 7: Desolation Sound — Layover
LOCATION:Prideaux Haven or Tenedos Bay
DESCRIPTION:Overnight: Prideaux Haven or Tenedos Bay\n\nNote: This layover is well earned. Desolation Sound gets its name from a gloomy 1792 survey — ignore that. In July it's the warmest\, most beautiful anchorage on the BC coast.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=7
UID:day-7-20260712@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260713
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260714
SUMMARY:Day 8: Desolation Sound → Campbell River (fuel) → Port Neville
LOCATION:Port Neville anchorage or Thurston Bay Marine Park
DESCRIPTION:77.2 NM · ~4.7 hrs\nOvernight: Port Neville anchorage or Thurston Bay Marine Park\n\nNote: This is a coordinated day: depart Desolation early\, fuel Campbell River at ~10:30am\, Seymour Narrows at slack midday\, anchor Port Neville by mid-afternoon. At 15 kts this is ~7.5 hrs total but the Narrows wait may be built in. Brief lunch at Campbell River fuel dock.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=8
UID:day-8-20260713@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260713T070000
DTEND:20260713T090300
SUMMARY:🚢 Desolation Sound → Campbell River BC
DESCRIPTION:24.7 NM · ~2h 3m\nDesolation Sound → Campbell River BC
UID:route-170e20aa-8bed-4e94-8ec6-4abc1e369811@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20260713T100000
DTEND:20260713T123800
SUMMARY:🚢 Campbell River BC → Port Neville
DESCRIPTION:52.5 NM · ~2h 38m\nCampbell River BC → Port Neville
UID:route-c03997e5-b42d-4a44-965d-2edd468800d4@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260714
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260715
SUMMARY:Day 9: Port Neville → Telegraph Cove
LOCATION:Telegraph Cove Marina or nearby anchorage
DESCRIPTION:33.7 NM · ~2.3 hrs\nOvernight: Telegraph Cove Marina or nearby anchorage\n\nNote: Relaxed day after yesterday's long push. Take your time through Johnstone Strait — the orca viewing here is as good as it gets on the BC coast.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=9
UID:day-9-20260714@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Day 10: Telegraph Cove → Broughtons / Lagoon Cove
LOCATION:Lagoon Cove Marina\, East Cracroft Island
DESCRIPTION:22.8 NM · ~2.3 hrs\nOvernight: Lagoon Cove Marina\, East Cracroft Island\n\nNote: Arriving early gives you the afternoon to explore and get oriented. Tonight: Kelly & Dan's famous prawn potluck — they supply the prawns\, you bring an appetizer. Unmissable.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=10
UID:day-10-20260715@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260716
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260717
SUMMARY:Day 11: Broughton Islands — Layover
LOCATION:Lagoon Cove or Echo Bay
DESCRIPTION:Overnight: Lagoon Cove or Echo Bay\n\nNote: Book Knight Inlet Lodge or Tide Rip Grizzly Tours in advance — this is a genuine bucket-list experience. Seeing a grizzly from the water in its natural habitat with the kids is unforgettable.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=11
UID:day-11-20260716@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260717
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260718
SUMMARY:Day 12: Lagoon Cove → Blind Channel Resort
LOCATION:Blind Channel Resort\, West Thurlow Island
DESCRIPTION:47.8 NM · ~8.4 hrs\nOvernight: Blind Channel Resort\, West Thurlow Island\n\nNote: Call ahead on VHF 66A to reserve a slip — Blind Channel fills up in summer. Easy run today\; enjoy the slow pace.
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=2026%20Summer%20Cruise&day=12
UID:day-12-20260717@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
